## Schedule

All six interviews completed Wednesday–Friday of Week 1. Each session: 25–30 minutes, by phone or video call. Notes captured live and uploaded as transcripts to `/research/transcripts/`.

## Cross-group coordination

Interview questions were cross-checked in the cohort-wide Research and Testing check-in so all six groups asked roughly the same things. This makes findings comparable across the cohort.

## Interview questions (6 neutral, open-ended)

The questions were deliberately broad to avoid leading the participant toward our hypotheses.

1. Tell me about your first two weeks at your current job. What did you spend most of your time doing?
2. When you needed to find a piece of information at work — a policy, a process, a contact — where did you usually start? Walk me through the last time that happened.
3. Have you ever wanted to ask a question at work but decided not to? What stopped you?
4. How many different tools or apps do you use in a typical workday? Is that a problem for you, or is it fine?
5. Have you used any AI tools at work? If yes, did you trust them? Why or why not?
6. If you could change one thing about how new people are onboarded at your company, what would it be?

## Consent

Before each interview, participants were told:
- The recording would be used only for academic and product-discovery purposes.
- They could stop the interview at any time.
- Their name and employer would not appear in the transcripts (sectors only).

